![Episode65.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578251895203-PNG3SW86V94DJEXCYGX2/Episode65.jpg)

Oh No! Captain Marvel is out in a few days and you haven't got a clue who Carol Danvers is?! Well luckily for you the guys at CBC have revved up for a Crash Course on all things CAPTAIN MARVEL aka Carol Danvers just in time for her Marvel Cinematic Universe debut! Starting at her old-school origin and going into what makes Carol who she is, we try and guess what took Marvel so long to crown her as its top female superhero. Learn how the character drastically changed starting in 2012 when writer Kelly Sue DeConnick took the reigns and what motivated DeConnick to tally revamp Captain Marvel!

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
